rComments: Do not take his course. You probably won't listen but the least I can do is prevent others from taking his courses.   He will fail you on purpose if you don't go to class. He marks the final exams himself; if he sees that you didn't go to class (which he could tell by the zeros you got from missing pop quizzes), he will mark your exam really hard.
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader']

rComments: Millman is great - he really cares about his students. The course is tough, but there's not much he can do about that  - he realizes how difficult it can be for students, and really goes the extra mile to help you.
Good prof, if you can follow: sometimes he's chalkboard writing is sloppy and he switches from one theme to another. Not bad, at all.

Highly chaotic chalkboard makes it impossible to take effective notes. Reading the textbook is far more effective than attending lectures. Unrealistic expectations demand that you be an outlier in order to avoid having your GPA decimated.

Seems completely oblivious to the students. Did not seem to notice that after 2 weeks only about 15 of 100 people were still coming to his completely pointless lectures. Absolutely hilarious strong French accent
